# Product CRUD Rule

- Keep Product CRUD business logic in `useProductStore` actions; keep pages/components focused on UI composition.
- Use `ProductCreate` for create flows and `ProductUpdate` for patch flows; do not collapse them into a single ambiguous type.
- For update payloads, only send defined fields; treat `undefined` as "no change".
- Keep image handling consistent with existing store behavior (`File` upload then map to `{ id, url }`).
- Keep create page footer as the submit trigger via exposed form `submit()`; avoid duplicating submit logic in page and form.
- Preserve zero `orig_sell_price` confirmation guard before create/update.
- Keep relation mapping explicit: map UI objects to `category_codes`, `tag_ids`, and `brand_codes` just before submit.
- Use `successNotification`/`failedNotification` and loading flags (`loading`, `adding`, `updating`) for every CRUD action path.
